import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['engineers'], data['population'])
    plt.xlabel('Percentage of Engineers')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the percentage of engineers and the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='state', y='engineers', legend=False)
    max_engineers_state = data.loc[data['engineers'].idxmax()]['state']
    max_engineers_value = data['engineers'].max()
    ax.axhline(max_engineers_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_engineers_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("Which state has the highest percentage of engineers?")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
